commentTextItems.html: worked to mid on and they charge through

commentPostTextItems.html: And there it is! What a brilliant chase from this young side. Shehzad was the star with a glorious 110 of only 112 balls. As the innings progressed they hit over the top superbly and found the gaps in the field. It was an impressive batting display.
The Afghans are gathered in a tight huddle, this is such a richly deserved victory. Looking forward as they improve as a cricket nation it will be victories like this that galvanise the team
The Man of the Match is Mohammed Shehzad, once again, his was a tremendous effort.
Disappointment no doubt for the Dutch, they struggled with the bat and the bowling and fielding weren't up to a great standard.

As the crowd of Afghan supporters continue to merrily beat their drums and tambourines, this is where we shall say goodbye to you all. Thank you for joining us at the VRA Ground but for now it's goodbye.

commentTextItems.html: skied off drive, mid off can't reach it
pushed to mid off
angled in and defended on the off side
smashed straight all the way along the ground! Glorious stroke

milestones.description: Bas Zuiderent has broken the record for most ducks (5) in ODIs for NED, going past Peter Borren's 4
Hamid Hassan has become the top wicket-taker for AFG in ODIs with 6 wickets, going past Shapoor's 4
Shahzad has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (44) in an innings in ODIs for AFG, going past Noor Ali's 36
Hamid Hassan has conceded the most runs in an innings (63) in ODIs for AFG, going past Samiullah Shinwari's record of 56
Asghar Afghan and Shahzad's 79-run partnership is AFG's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 40 between Noor Ali and Shahzad
Samiullah Shinwari and Shahzad's 81-run partnership is AFG's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 40 between Mohammad Nabi and Asghar Afghan
Mohammad Nabi and Samiullah Shinwari's 14-run partnership is AFG's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 10 between Raees and Asghar Afghan
Shahzad's 110 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for AFG), surpassing Mohammad Nabi's 58
This is the highest match aggregate (463) involving teams Netherlands & Afghanistan in ODIs
Shahzad has become the top scorer for AFG in ODIs with 126 runs, going past Samiullah Shinwari's 79
Jeroen Smits has broken the record for most ODIs (17) as captain for NED, going past van Troost
Asghar Afghan has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (3) for AFG, going past Hamid Hassan
